### =============================================================
### Event Ingestion Service — REST Client Test Suite
### Install: VS Code "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client)
### Run: click "Send Request" above any ### block
### =============================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api/v1
@validTenant = tenant-abc
@anotherTenant = tenant-xyz


### =============================================================
### 1. HAPPY PATH — successful event ingestion + processing
###    Assessment: validates body, extracts tenantId, saves to DB,
###    pushes job, processor marks status = processed
### =============================================================

### [1a] Basic user_action event → expect 202 + eventId
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

{
  "type": "user_action",
  "payload": {
    "action": "clicked_button"
  }
}

###

### [1b] system_event type → expect 202 (processor no-op branch)
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

{
  "type": "system_event",
  "payload": {
    "source": "cron",
    "trigger": "daily_sync"
  }
}

###

### [1c] Unknown type → expect 202, processor logs warning but succeeds
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

{
  "type": "unknown_custom_type",
  "payload": {
    "custom": true
  }
}


### =============================================================
### 2. TENANT ISOLATION (CRITICAL)
###    Assessment: tenantId extracted from header, validated,
###    all DB queries scoped to tenant
### =============================================================

### [2a] Different tenant — creates isolated record, no cross-tenant bleed
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{anotherTenant}}

{
  "type": "user_action",
  "payload": {
    "action": "logged_in",
    "userId": "u_999"
  }
}

###

### [2b] Missing x-tenant-id header → expect 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "user_action",
  "payload": {
    "action": "clicked_button"
  }
}

###

### [2c] Empty x-tenant-id header → expect 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id:

{
  "type": "user_action",
  "payload": {
    "action": "clicked_button"
  }
}

###

### [2d] Whitespace-only tenant → expect 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id:    

{
  "type": "user_action",
  "payload": {
    "action": "clicked_button"
  }
}


### =============================================================
### 3. REQUEST VALIDATION (class-validator)
###    Assessment: ValidationPipe with whitelist + forbidNonWhitelisted
### =============================================================

### [3a] Missing `type` field → expect 400 with field error
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

{
  "payload": {
    "action": "clicked_button"
  }
}

###

### [3b] Missing `payload` field → expect 400 with field error
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

{
  "type": "user_action"
}

###

### [3c] `type` is not a string → expect 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

{
  "type": 123,
  "payload": {}
}

###

### [3d] `payload` is not an object (string instead) → expect 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

{
  "type": "user_action",
  "payload": "this_should_be_an_object"
}

###

### [3e] Extra unknown field → expect 400 (forbidNonWhitelisted)
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

{
  "type": "user_action",
  "payload": { "action": "test" },
  "unknownField": "should_be_rejected"
}

###

### [3f] Empty body → expect 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

{}

###

### [3g] Empty type string → expect 400 (@IsNotEmpty)
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

{
  "type": "",
  "payload": { "action": "test" }
}


### =============================================================
### 4. RETRY STRATEGY — exponential backoff, 3 attempts
###    Assessment: payload.fail = true triggers simulated failure
###    Watch logs: retry_attempt × 2 → processing_failed
###    DB status transitions: pending → failed
### =============================================================

### [4a] Force failure — triggers 3 attempts then marks status=failed
###      Check logs for: retry_attempt (×2) then processing_failed
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

{
  "type": "user_action",
  "payload": {
    "action": "will_fail",
    "fail": true
  }
}

###

### [4b] Fail on tenant-xyz — same retry flow, isolated to that tenant
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{anotherTenant}}

{
  "type": "system_event",
  "payload": {
    "fail": true,
    "reason": "downstream_unavailable"
  }
}


### =============================================================
### 5. STRUCTURED LOGGING VERIFICATION
###    Assessment: every job lifecycle must emit JSON log events
###    Run any request above then inspect stdout for these events:
###
###    SUCCESS FLOW logs to watch:
###      { "event": "received",            "attempt": 0 }
###      { "event": "processing_started",  "attempt": 1 }
###      { "event": "processing_success",  "attempt": 1 }
###
###    FAILURE FLOW logs to watch:
###      { "event": "received",            "attempt": 0 }
###      { "event": "processing_started",  "attempt": 1 }
###      { "event": "retry_attempt",       "attempt": 1 }
###      { "event": "processing_started",  "attempt": 2 }
###      { "event": "retry_attempt",       "attempt": 2 }
###      { "event": "processing_started",  "attempt": 3 }
###      { "event": "processing_failed",   "attempt": 3 }
### =============================================================

### [5a] Trigger full success log chain
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

{
  "type": "user_action",
  "payload": {
    "action": "log_chain_test"
  }
}

###

### [5b] Trigger full failure + retry log chain
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

{
  "type": "user_action",
  "payload": {
    "fail": true,
    "action": "log_retry_chain_test"
  }
}


### =============================================================
### 6. RICH PAYLOAD VARIANTS
###    Assessment: payload is free-form JSON (Record<string,unknown>)
### =============================================================

### [6a] Nested payload
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

{
  "type": "user_action",
  "payload": {
    "action": "form_submitted",
    "user": {
      "id": "u_123",
      "plan": "pro"
    },
    "form": {
      "id": "onboarding",
      "step": 3
    },
    "timestamp": "2024-01-15T10:00:00Z"
  }
}

###

### [6b] Minimal payload (empty object is valid)
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

{
  "type": "heartbeat",
  "payload": {}
}


### =============================================================
### 7. EDGE CASES
### =============================================================

### [7a] Very long tenantId (should still work — no length constraint)
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: tenant-org-acme-corp-division-east-team-backend-prod

{
  "type": "user_action",
  "payload": { "action": "test" }
}

###

### [7b] Numeric values in payload (JSON types preserved in DB)
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

{
  "type": "analytics",
  "payload": {
    "score": 98.6,
    "count": 42,
    "active": true,
    "tags": ["a", "b", "c"]
  }
}

###

### [7c] Wrong HTTP method → expect 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/events
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

###

### [7d] Wrong Content-Type (no JSON body parse) → expect 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: text/plain
x-tenant-id: {{validTenant}}

type=user_action
